ring changed to an [e] at the end of sentences. Body is pronounced as 'bæde' instead of 'bɑdi.' Most common is the lengthening of vowels in certain situations (see below), such as before rhotics or fricatives. %0a%3c %0a%3c I also wanted to briefly note the use of Scottish English to impart prestige on the company's alcohol products as notable. %0a%3c %0a%3c Sources:%0a%3c https://www.thespiritsbusiness.com/2016/03/watchdog-rejects-complaint-about-racist-aldi-whisky-ad/%0a%3c https://www.thenational.scot/news/14902122.aldis-scottish-accent-translation-ad-not-racist/%0a%3c https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scottish_vowel_length_rule%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: B:)%0a%3c (:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
